<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id0c772969-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s67"><num value="67">§ 67.</num><heading> Right of repeal</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Congress may alter, amend, add to, or repeal any of the provisions of sections 41 to 46, 48, 50, 51 to 53, and 54 to 57, of this title; but no contract or individual right made or acquired under such provisions shall be thereby divested or impaired.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id0c77296a-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795">(R.S. § 5594.)</sourceCredit>
